<subSubSection id="F15FC7327CBC09C781D327A945C9B68F" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" type="notes">
<paragraph id="1F6CC980B9F995932997A2F4E6643E4B" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A2F4CB9D49F78D9D559946B997851AA6" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<taxonomicName id="6B304B9E02B8CCBAF266564F8CEE512F" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Ceratostomataceae" genus="Microthecium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Microthecium brevirostrum" order="Melanosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="brevirostrum">Microthecium brevirostrum</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4B23475FAD181AD2EF680DFC36167575" genus="Mi." lsidName="Mi. fallax" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="fallax">Mi. fallax</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="49731F6F7D7B85982638B490B5F617D8" genus="Mi." lsidName="Mi. fimbriatum" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="fimbriatum">Mi. fimbriatum</taxonomicName>
produce ostiolate ascomata and ellipsoidal to citriform, often plataniform, smooth-walled ascospores with an apiculate germ pore at each end. 
<taxonomicName id="D7C55F330FB042A64B945BA0DB46BB6C" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Ceratostomataceae" genus="Microthecium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Microthecium fimbriatum" order="Melanosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="fimbriatum">Microthecium fimbriatum</taxonomicName>
is easily distinguished by its smaller (100-110 
<normalizedToken id="368C8E43E0A514111CC177090BE85F55" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
diam.), reddish ascomata, while 
<taxonomicName id="F88F0775CC05C959103A79E6F42EF2EC" genus="Mi." lsidName="Mi. fallax" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="fallax">Mi. fallax</taxonomicName>
differs in the production of bulbils.
</paragraph>
